EU REACH — regulates chemical substances manufactured or imported into the EU above 1 tonne/year.
US RCRA — governs the disposal of solid and hazardous waste.
Basel Convention — restricts transboundary movements of hazardous wastes.
EU Waste Framework Directive — establishes the waste hierarchy and end-of-waste criteria.
US OSHA HCS — requires SDS and labeling for hazardous chemicals.
EU RoHS — restricts hazardous materials in electrical and electronic equipment.
US Superfund Act — provides authority for hazardous waste site cleanup.
ISO 14001 — environmental management systems framework.
EU IED BAT — emission limits for industrial installations based on best available techniques.
UN GHS Rev.9 — international standard for hazard classification and labelling.
US TSCA — regulates introduction of new or existing chemicals in the US.
EU WEEE — collection, recycling and recovery targets for electronic waste.
MARPOL Convention — regulates marine pollution from ships.
EU ETS — cap-and-trade system for greenhouse gas emissions.
Stockholm Convention — bans or restricts persistent organic pollutants.
EU CLP — aligns EU chemical classification with the GHS.
IAEA General Safety Requirements — radiation protection and safety of radioactive waste.
EU Packaging and Packaging Waste Directive — sets recycling and recovery targets for packaging.
